<seg id="23"> In addition, the Pakistani Foreign Ministry issued a statement on the evening of the 15th strongly condemning the shooting incident that killed three Chinese engineers that afternoon, calling the incident an act of terrorism. </seg>
<seg id="24"> The statement said that the Pakistani government and people strongly condemned the shooting incident that killed the Chinese engineers. </seg>
<seg id="25"> The Pakistani government and people expressed deep respect for the Chinese engineers who had given their lives for the development of Pakistan. </seg>
<seg id="26"> The Pakistani government and people expressed deep condolences for the families of the dead. </seg>
<seg id="27"> The statement also said that the Pakistani government is determined to strengthen protection of Chinese citizens working in Pakistan. </seg>
<seg id="28"> The government will take all measures to prevent similar incidents from reoccurring in future. </seg>
<seg id="29"> The statement also said that the killing of the three Chinese engineers was an act of terrorism in an attempt to create (()) in the relations between Pakistan and China. </seg>
<seg id="30"> The Pakistani government will never allow such attempt to materialize. </seg>
<seg id="31"> Pakistani law enforcement authorities are currently taking steps to swiftly catch the killers and bring them to justice. </seg>
<seg id="32"> In addition, Chinese State President Hu Jintao learned late at night on the 15th about the shooting of the Chinese engineering and technical personnel in the province of Balochistan, Pakistan, which left three people dead. </seg>
<seg id="33"> Er, upon learning the news, he showed great concern over the safety of Chinese engineering and technical personnel in Pakistan. </seg>
<seg id="34"> Well, Hu Jintao, he immediately instructed the Foreign Ministry and the Chinese embassy and consulate in Pakistan to request the Pakistani side to capture the killers, to ensure, um, the safety of Chinese nationals, personnel in Pakistan, er, to properly address the aftermath of the death of the victims. </seg>
<seg id="35"> In addition, Hu Jintao also expressed deep condolences on the tragic death of the Chinese personnel and expressed sincere sympathy for the families of the victims. </seg>
<seg id="36"> All right, regarding this issue, let's now connect with Chen Yiming, People's Daily correspondent in Islamabad, to find out the latest development. </seg>
<seg id="37"> Hello, Mr. Chen. </seg>
<seg id="38"> Please brief us on the latest development of the investigation of the shooting death of the Chinese engineers. </seg>
<seg id="39"> Er, yes, host. </seg>
<seg id="40"> Er, according to what I have learned from the Chinese consulate general in Karachi, er, the Chinese embassy and consulate has already informed the victims' work unit of this tragic incident. </seg>
<seg id="41"> Well, according to the general practice, um, the work unit of the victims should be consulting with the families before making any final decision as to how to deal with the aftermath. </seg>
<seg id="42"> In addition, the Pakistani Foreign Ministry also issued a statement yesterday. </seg>
<seg id="43"> He, er, the statement indicated that the perpetuators of the incident attempted to sow discord in the relations between China and Pakistan. </seg>
<seg id="44"> Er, the statement said that there will be a thorough investigation into the incident and that Pakistan will strengthen security protection of all Chinese working in this country.  In addition, it said that Pakistan will try all it can to prevent similar incidents from reoccurring. </seg>
<seg id="45"> Er, in addition, according to the report by Pakistan's private-run GEO on the evening of the 15th, Bashir, chief executive officer of the Attock cement factory in Pakistan, said in his interview with the station this evening that following the attack, the Pakistani side will try to arrange for the remaining 11 Chinese engineering and technical personnel working on the construction site of the cement project to return to their country as soon as possible. </seg>
<seg id="46"> Well, um, Bashir also said in the interview that with regard to the question of some Pakistani media why the Chinese engineers did not have security guards with them when the incident took place, er, he said, er, actually the cement factory where these engineers worked has its own security system; however, since the incident occurred within the boundary of the factory, none of security guards were with them at the time. </seg>
<seg id="47"> Well, he expressed deep regrets about the occurrence of this tragic incident. </seg>
<seg id="48"> Host. </seg>
<seg id="49"> Eh, all right. </seg>
<seg id="50"> Er, besides, it is actually not the first time that Chinese engineering personnel were killed in attacks in Pakistan. </seg>
<seg id="51"> Such an incident occurred in October 2004. </seg>
<seg id="52"> Two Chinese engineers were kidnapped by an armed group in South Waziristan. </seg>
<seg id="53"> In the end, one of them unfortunately died during the rescue mission. </seg>
<seg id="54"> In addition, three engineering personnel also died in a bombing attack in Gwadar in May of the same year. </seg>
<seg id="55"> Let's have a recap. </seg>
<seg id="56"> On May 3, 2004, in the port of Gwadar in the southern part of the province of Balochistan, Pakistan, a vehicle carrying 12 Chinese was hit by a car bomb while it was driving to the port construction site. </seg>
<seg id="57"> In the end three Chinese engineering personnel died, while nine people were wounded. </seg>
<seg id="58"> This attack was believed to be launched by local separatists and tribal militias. </seg>
<seg id="59"> On October 9 of the same year, two Chinese engineers were kidnapped by gunmen in South Waziristan where Pakistan borders Afghanistan. </seg>
<seg id="60"> When Pakistani troops came to the rescue of the hostages later, one engineer was unfortunately shot to death. </seg>
<seg id="61"> However, armed groups linked with al-Qaeda rather than separatist militants were believed to be responsible for this hostage incident. </seg>
<seg id="62"> Since China has a close economic exchange with Pakistan and participates in Pakistan's infrastructure construction, quite a number of Chinese engineering personnel are working there. </seg>
<seg id="63"> Yet, tribal militias in Pakistan accused the government of robbing them of their natural resources. </seg>
<seg id="64"> Consequently, Chinese people have fallen victims several times to attacks and abductions. </seg>
<seg id="65"> This comprehensive report has been brought to you by Phoenix Satellite V. </seg>
</doc>
<doc docid="PHOENIX_GOODMORNCN_CMN_20060215_185801_955_1163.qrtr" genre="broadcast_news" sysid="E01">
<seg id="1"> Let's look at a few Japan-related news items. </seg>
<seg id="2"> Recently there has been a rather shocking piece of news in Japanese political circles. </seg>
<seg id="3"> That is, Tsuneo Watanabe, chairman of the Yomiuri Shimbun, the number one in the Japanese media, he ordered the Yomiuri Shimbun to publish some articles against Koizumi's visit to Yasukuni Shrine.  Furthermore, the Yomiuri Shimbun has since taken a position against Koizumi's visit to Yasukuni Shrine. </seg>
<seg id="4"> Er, well, um, Tsuneo Watanabe, he was lashing out against Koizumi in his speech a few days ago, saying he is very ignorant and has no knowledge of any history or culture. </seg>
<seg id="5"> At the same time he also said that visiting Yasukuni Shrine is like singing praises of Hitler.  In addition, he said that by doing so, Koizumi also made China and South Korea consider Japan a very dangerous country.  This is going to have no end of trouble. </seg>
<seg id="6"> Well, why could Tsuneo Watanabe, his attitude trigger great impact? </seg>
<seg id="7"> Actually, he is also very influential in political circles and has been a manipulator behind the scenes all along. </seg>
<seg id="8"> Yet, he used to be a very rightist figure. </seg>
<seg id="9"> We should say he had always supported hawks and also pushed vigorously for constitutional amendment. </seg>
<seg id="10"> But now, ah, this is really a big turn. </seg>
<seg id="11"> He now directed his attacks against Koizumi and started to oppose such a stance. </seg>
<seg id="12"> Actually in 2004 when someone attacked Koizumi for visiting Yasukuni Shrine, um, Tsuneo Watanabe, he still said, he said, er, he supported him and wanted Koizumi to resist the pressure. </seg>
<seg id="13"> However, he gave a speech recently.  He said, I am already more than 80 years old and don't have much time left. </seg>
<seg id="14"> Well, he has now adopted a high-sounding tone and taken on a kind of highly anti-war stance in his speech. </seg>
<seg id="15"> This kind of changing sides by him, of course, has a great social impact in Japan. </seg>
<seg id="16"> Just like Tsuneo Watanabe said himself, he said, I firmly believe I have the actual power of controlling and changing the political orientation. </seg>
<seg id="17"> Furthermore, he also said that should the Yomiuri Shimbun's freedom of speech and freedom of coverage and compilation be under the government pressure, he would resist it at the risk of his life. </seg>
<seg id="18"> Well, what kind of situation has it come to now? </seg>
<seg id="19"> That is, the Yomiuri Shimbun, the largest newspaper in Japan, and the Asahi Shimbun, the second largest newspaper in Japan, now these two large newspapers have started to join hands in opposing Koizumi's visit to Yasukuni Shrine. </seg>
<seg id="20"> Originally, these two large newspapers were opponents, but later when the two chairmen met, they at least reached consensus on this issue. </seg>
<seg id="21"> As a result, they now both launched massive attacks on Koizumi, forming what we could call a dream team. </seg>
<seg id="22"> Actually, these two large newspapers of theirs should have a very large influence on Japanese mainstream public opinion. </seg>
<seg id="23"> In addition, let's look at the meeting of Japan's House of Representatives.  At one of their recent meetings, two relatively popular candidates for successor to Japanese Prime Minister Junichiro Koizumi made the same remark. </seg>
<seg id="24"> Who are these two people? </seg>
<seg id="25"> One is Chief Cabinet Secretary Shinzo Abe, and the other is Japanese Foreign Minister Taro Aso, who has made a series of appalling remarks recently. </seg>
<seg id="26"> What remarks did these two make? </seg>
<seg id="27"> They said that Japan's WWII criminals were not criminals. </seg>
<seg id="28"> What they meant was, er, it was the international court that has called them criminals and convicted them. </seg>
<seg id="29"> Whereas, in Japan, according to the international law, they were; according to the domestic law in Japan, er, the war criminals did not violate the domestic law of Japan. </seg>
<seg id="30"> Therefore, they think that WWII criminals should not be considered criminals in Japan. </seg>
<seg id="31"> At the same time, um, Shinzo Abe, he also mentioned that Japan should now focus its vision on the whole world and develop relations with the United States and develop commercial and trade relations with, um, some east Asian countries.  In addition, it should also try its best to develop close ties with India.  It should not always focus on China. </seg>
</doc>
<doc docid="groups.google.com_LNTS_14974749cb4b6f49_CMN_20060216_084900" genre="newsgroup" sysid="E01">
<hl>
<seg id="1"> Championship Hopeful but not Assured </seg>
</hl>
<poster>
<seg id="2"> Love Life, Love Luneng </seg>
</poster>
<seg id="3"> The fire will soon be lit on the battlefield of the Chinese Super League. </seg>
<seg id="4"> Luneng Taishan is getting ready for the new season and preparing to fight again for the championship. </seg>
<seg id="5"> The fight for the championship among Dalian, Shandong, and Shanghai is on the verge of breaking out. </seg>
<seg id="6"> Who will win the championship in the end? </seg>
<seg id="7"> Based on an analysis of strength, although the Taishan team has great hopes of winning the championship, it is not 100 percent assured. </seg>
<seg id="8"> First, new team members have little time to get adjusted. </seg>
<seg id="9"> The Taishan team had four major openings last year. </seg>
<seg id="10"> This year, following recruitment of the two famous national football players Li Leilei and Wang Liang, the Taishan team will soon be joined by two foreign players.  Its strength should be said to have increased without decreasing. </seg>
<seg id="11"> However, since the national team is preparing for matches with Palestine and Iraq, there has hardly been any coordination between the national team players and their teammates. </seg>
<seg id="12"> By the time they return to the team, the Super League will be starting. </seg>
<seg id="13"> Therefore, the problem of getting adjusted is the biggest problem the Taishan team now faces. </seg>
<seg id="14"> In my opinion, the national football players can serve as substitutes in the first few Super League matches. </seg>
<seg id="15"> First, the games can be used as practice to get the team adjusted. </seg>
<seg id="16"> Second, it can allow the players who have just finished two group matches with the national team to take a rest. </seg>
<seg id="17"> After sharpening their skills in several matches, it will not be too late to enter the battle. </seg>
<seg id="18"> The next problem is the hidden troubles on defense. </seg>
<seg id="19"> Last year, the Taishan team's defense was criticized by football fans. </seg>
<seg id="20"> This year, defense has been improved somewhat with the recruitment of Li Leilei, but it's not yet time to rest easy. </seg>
<seg id="21"> The central back still has a problem with turning around slowly, while the substitute players are either slightly old or lack sufficient experience. </seg>
<seg id="22"> If the central back can put forth a stable performance this year, then the Taishan team will have a greater chance of winning the championship. </seg>
<seg id="23"> I think it may be a good idea to use Ren Yongshun, who is in good physical shape.  Despite insufficient experience, he can test himself this year and prepare for the future. </seg>
<seg id="24"> In addition, it is also fine to recall Gao Yao to play sweeper. </seg>
<seg id="25"> There are quite a few members of the Taishan team who can play defensive midfield.  Both Cui Peng and Haibin can play. </seg>
<seg id="26"> Gao Yao, who is physically strong and fierce in intercepting the ball, should be able to do a good job as central back. </seg>
<seg id="27"> Also, whether the foreign players can adjust themselves... </seg>
<seg id="28"> Issues with foreign players have constantly been a big problem for the Taishan team. </seg>
<seg id="29"> Last year, Danciulescu's performance left much to be desired. </seg>
<seg id="30"> I know the foreign players for this year have not been determined yet. </seg>
<seg id="31"> I think that this year, in addition to recruiting an excellent striker, a pure left midfielder should be recruited. </seg>
<seg id="32"> Except for Xing Rui a few years ago, the Taishan team has not had a single true left-footed specialist. </seg>
<seg id="33"> Although Cui Peng and others are all competent, however, a real left midfielder is still much better than a stand-in. </seg>
<seg id="34"> If these three problems can be resolved well, the road to the championship for the Taishan team should be a bit smoother. </seg>
<seg id="35"> As a Shandong football fan, I hope very much that the Taishan team will win the championship this year. </seg>
<seg id="36"> However, to be honest, based on this year's competitive situation, the Taishan team has great hopes but there are few assurances. </seg>
</doc>
<doc docid="groups.google.com_brandvista_4a454bf36d4bd92a_CMN_20060210_062400" genre="newsgroup" sysid="E01">
<hl>
<seg id="1"> Batey Ads Merges with JWT Network, Would It be Too Late to Say Happy New Year? </seg>
</hl>
<poster>
<seg id="2"> BrandVista Post: </seg>
</poster>
<seg id="3"> Hello, everyone. </seg>
<seg id="4"> Once again Spring Festival is behind us.  Our friends who combined their vacation days with Spring Festival holidays are returning to their work. </seg>
<seg id="5"> Wish all friends a Happy New Year, if it is still not too late to say Happy New Year. </seg>
<seg id="6"> When I was chatting with NPLCN in a cafe the other day, he mentioned the current BrandVista. </seg>
<seg id="7"> The website has become much prettier. </seg>
<seg id="8"> The layout of the content is pretty good. </seg>
<seg id="9"> What he likes most is still the recent fully revamped Discuz-based community BBS. </seg>
<seg id="10"> Speaking of the community, I will have to thank one person. </seg>
<seg id="11"> That is Mr. Li Mingshun, general manager of Discuz Beijing company. </seg>
<seg id="12"> If you search for his name on Google, you can get a lot of hits. </seg>
<seg id="13"> I roughly know that he used to be at Sina and later started his own business, an internet ad exchange platform for small and medium-sized businesses, similar to adbrite.com abroad. </seg>
<seg id="14"> At that time he debated on MSN to the effect that Vista thinks that the development of many sectors in China all depends on private economy and growth of small and medium-sized businesses. </seg>
<seg id="15"> However, the situation in this respect in China's markets now is not encouraging. </seg>
<seg id="16"> Therefore, the creative media sector and the similar consulting sector serving small and medium-sized businesses are unable to grow into large scale. </seg>
<seg id="17"> Charging higher fees to facilitate its own development eventually led to an unfulfilling cycle. </seg>
<seg id="18"> Later he came to Discuz. </seg>
<seg id="19"> Discuz is an excellent community software based on PHP and MySQL database. </seg>
<seg id="20"> With the help of Ramboo, a technical engineer in Beijing, the BrandVista community finally saw hope again and emerged with a brand-new look. </seg>
<seg id="21"> The feedback is excellent. </seg>
<seg id="22"> The interface is clean-cut and friendly. </seg>
<seg id="23"> The speed is quite fast. </seg>
<seg id="24"> Writing some texts inspirational both to myself and to others on a freshly clean-cut interface and exchanging details in my work and life with friends of the same aspiration working in the same industry, I started to think this is a kind of happiness. </seg>
<seg id="25"> Thanks, Discuz! </seg>
<seg id="26"> There has been quite a lot of news lately in the advertising sector. </seg>
<seg id="27"> Starting from January, the WTO regulations on the liberalization of advertising went into effect. </seg>
<seg id="28"> Large foreign companies have been arriving at the scene, while smaller foreign companies are getting ready.  Prosperity seems to be everywhere. </seg>
