<seg id="45"> Er, besides, according to the nightly report of the er, privately-run GEO in Pakistan, Bashir, the Chief Executive Officer of Attock Cement Factory in Pakistan, said during an interview with the station that night that after the attack, Pakistan will arrange well, for the return of the remaining 11 Chinese engineers working on this cement project to China as soon as possible. </seg>
<seg id="46"> Bashir also said in the interview that some Pakistani media questioned why er, the Chinese engineers were not accompanied by security officers, er, when the incident happened. Er, he said that er, in fact, the cement factory that the engineers er, worked for has its own security protection system. However, since the accident happened within the factory compound, thus no security officers were accompanying them when the accident happened. </seg>
<seg id="47"> Well, he er, expressed deep regret over this unfortunate incident. </seg>
<seg id="48"> Anchor. </seg>
<seg id="49"> Yes, good. </seg>
<seg id="50"> Er, moreover, this was indeed not the first time that Chinese engineers have been murdered in Pakistan. </seg>
<seg id="51"> Such an incident happened in October 2004. </seg>
<seg id="52"> Two Chinese engineers were kidnapped by a militant group in South Waziristan. </seg>
<seg id="53"> Eventually, one of the people was unfortunately killed during the rescue effort. </seg>
<seg id="54"> Moreover, in May of the same year, three engineers were killed by a bomb in Gwadar. </seg>
<seg id="55"> Let us review the incidents. </seg>
<seg id="56"> On May 3, 2004, at the Gwadar port south of the Balochistan province, Pakistan, a vehicle carrying 12 Chinese was attacked by a car bomb on its way to the work site at the port. </seg>
<seg id="57"> Three Chinese engineers were killed and nine others were injured in the end. </seg>
<seg id="58"> The attack was believed to have been launched by local separatists and tribal insurgents. </seg>
<seg id="59"> On October 9 of the same year, two Chinese engineers were kidnapped by insurgents in the South Waziristan district at the Pakistan-Afghanistan border. </seg>
<seg id="60"> An engineer was unfortunately shot to death when the Pakistani troops later rescued the hostages. </seg>
<seg id="61"> However, the kidnapping was believed to have been orchestrated by a militant group linked to al-Qaeda, and not by separatist insurgents. </seg>
<seg id="62"> Due to the frequent economic contacts between China and Pakistan, many Chinese engineers take part in Pakistani infrastructure projects and work in the local areas. </seg>
<seg id="63"> Tribal insurgents in Pakistan also accuse the government of seizing their natural resources. </seg>
<seg id="64"> As a result, Chinese have fallen victim to several attacks and kidnaps. </seg>
<seg id="65"> This is a news roundup by Phoenix TV. </seg>
</doc>
<doc docid="PHOENIX_GOODMORNCN_CMN_20060215_185801_955_1163.qrtr" genre="broadcast_news" sysid="E02">
<seg id="1"> Let's look at a few Japanese news items. </seg>
<seg id="2"> There is a rather shocking piece of news in Japanese politics recently. </seg>
<seg id="3"> Tsuneo Watanabe, President of The Yomiuri Shimbun, a leading outlet in Japan's media, instructed The Yomiuri Shimbun to publish um, articles criticizing Koizumi's visit to the Yasukuni Shrine. Since then, The Yomiuri Shimbun has held the same position on the matter. </seg>
<seg id="4"> Er, well, um, Tsuneo Watanabe railed against Koizumi in um, his speech a few days ago, calling him very ignorant, and that he does not know any history or culture. </seg>
<seg id="5"> He also equated the visitation of the Yasukuni Shrine to the glorification of Hitler. He added that such an act by Koizumi has made China and Korea consider Japan as an extremely dangerous nation, which will cause endless trouble. </seg>
<seg id="6"> Why would Tsuneo Watanabe's position create huge shock waves? </seg>
<seg id="7"> In fact, he is very influential in politics and has always been a hidden hand. </seg>
<seg id="8"> He had been a far rightist in the past. </seg>
<seg id="9"> He had supported the hawks and aggressively promoted the revision of the Constitution. </seg>
<seg id="10"> However, it is a um, huge turn now. </seg>
<seg id="11"> He has turned the cannon around to start bombing Koizumi and opposing such a position. </seg>
<seg id="12"> Actually, in 2004 when people criticized Koizumi for visiting the Yasukuni Shrine, um, Tsuneo Watanabe still claimed that, he claimed that he supported Koizumi, and asked him to stand up to the pressure. </seg>
<seg id="13"> Nonetheless, he made a speech recently saying, "I'll be 80 years old this year. I have very little time left." </seg>
<seg id="14"> Well, now he comes forward and makes anti-war speeches in a lofty tone. </seg>
<seg id="15"> His change in um, allegiance no doubt creates a huge impact on Japanese, um society. </seg>
<seg id="16"> As Tsuneo Watanabe put it himself, "I believe I have the confidence and the ability to change the political situation." </seg>
<seg id="17"> He added that if the government exerts pressure on the freedom of speech and assembly and the editorial freedom of The Yomiuri Shimbun, he would risk his life to resist. </seg>
<seg id="18"> Then, what kind of situation has been formed now? </seg>
<seg id="19"> Japan's largest newspaper, The Yomiuri Shimbun, and its second largest newspaper, um, the %pw Asahi Shimbun, the two major newspapers have joined hands in opposing Koizumi's visit to the Yasukuni Shrine. </seg>
<seg id="20"> Originally, the two major newspapers were two opposing groups. However, after the two presidents met, at least they had reached a consensus on this matter. </seg>
<seg id="21"> Thus, they both adopt strong offensives in um, railing against Koizumi. It can be said that they have formed a dream team. </seg>
<seg id="22"> In fact, these two major newspapers have huge, um, influence on the mainstream public opinion in Japan. </seg>
<seg id="23"> Moreover, let us look at the meeting of the um, House of Representatives in Japan. In a recent meeting, the same remark was made by the top two successor candidates um, of um, Japan's Prime Minister Junichiro Koizumi. </seg>
<seg id="24"> Who were these two people? </seg>
<seg id="25"> %pw one was Shinzo Abe, Chief Cabinet Secretary, and the other was Taro Aso, Japan's Foreign Minister, who has repeatedly made um, shocking remarks in recent days. </seg>
<seg id="26"> What remark did both of them make? </seg>
<seg id="27"> They both said that Japan's war criminals of the Second World War were not criminals. </seg>
<seg id="28"> What they meant was that er, it was the international court that called them um, criminals and convicted them. </seg>
<seg id="29"> While in Japan, according to international laws, according to Japanese laws, er, the war criminals had not broken any Japanese laws. </seg>
<seg id="30"> Thus, they argued that war criminals of the Second World War should not be considered as criminals in Japan. </seg>
<seg id="31"> In the meantime, um, Shinzo Abe mentioned that Japan should now have the whole world in view and develop its relationship with the United States and business and trading ties with um, East Asian countries. Moreover, it should develop close ties with India instead of focusing on China all the time. </seg>
</doc>
<doc docid="groups.google.com_LNTS_14974749cb4b6f49_CMN_20060216_084900" genre="newsgroup" sysid="E02">
<hl>
<seg id="1"> Championship Hopeful but Not a Sure Thing </seg>
</hl>
<poster>
<seg id="2"> Loving Life and Luneng </seg>
</poster>
<seg id="3"> The gunpowder smoke of the Chinese Super Cup Soccer Game will soon bring flames of war. </seg>
<seg id="4"> The Luneng Team of Taishan is ready for the new game season, and is preparing to rush to the championship again. </seg>
<seg id="5"> The battles for seizing dominance among Lian, Lu, and Hu, the three strong teams, will break out at any moment. </seg>
<seg id="6"> Who will win the championship at last? </seg>
<seg id="7"> Based on an analysis of actual strengths, although the Taishan Team has a great hope of seizing the championship, it has no full certainty of success. </seg>
<seg id="8"> First, the time for new team members to adapt to each other is short. </seg>
<seg id="9"> The Taishan Team had nothing new last year. </seg>
<seg id="10"> The Taishan Team introduced Li Leilei and Wang Liang, the two members from the national team, this year. Soon after that, it will also add two members to the team from foreign teams, and its actual strength should be seen as increased, not reduced. </seg>
<seg id="11"> But because the national team is preparing for the matches with the Palestinian and Iraqi teams, those members of the national team cannot coordinate with the members of this team. </seg>
<seg id="12"> When they return to the football club, the league matches will start right away, </seg>
<seg id="13"> So, the issue of adapting to each other is the biggest issue the Taishan Team is facing. </seg>
<seg id="14"> I think that those members from the national team can be substitute players for the first several rounds of games in the league matches. </seg>
<seg id="15"> Firstly, they can be trained to adapt to the team in matches; </seg>
<seg id="16"> secondly, those national team members who have played two group matches can have a rest. </seg>
<seg id="17"> After several rounds of matches, their edge would be honed, and it won't be too late for them to participate. </seg>
<seg id="18"> Second, its defense has hidden problems. </seg>
<seg id="19"> The defense of the Taishan Team was scolded as a sick one by its fans last year. </seg>
<seg id="20"> Li Leilei was introduced this year, and has improved the defense, but the team has not reached the time for sitting back and relaxing. </seg>
<seg id="21"> The problem of center halfbacks' and fullbacks' slowness in turning back still exists, and those substitute players are either older in age or lack experience. </seg>
<seg id="22"> If center halfbacks and fullbacks can solidly play their roles, the Taishan Team would have one more advantage in its path to seizing the championship. </seg>
<seg id="23"> I think that it does not hurt to use Ren Yongshun who has good physical qualities, although lacking experience. He can exercise this year in preparation for the future. </seg>
<seg id="24"> And also, it is OK to withdraw Gao Rao to play fullback. </seg>
<seg id="25"> Many members of the Taishan Team can play fullback, including Cui Peng and Hai Bin. </seg>
<seg id="26"> Gao Rao is strong physically, and can aggressively and fiercely intercept the ball, and should be able to do a good job in the position of either center halfback or fullback. </seg>
<seg id="27"> Third, whether foreign players can adapt to the team. </seg>
<seg id="28"> The introduction of foreign players is a big issue that has been puzzling the Taishan Team. </seg>
<seg id="29"> Nobody dares to say anything good about Dan Qiu's performance last year. </seg>
<seg id="30"> It is known that foreign players have not been selected for introduction for this year. </seg>
<seg id="31"> I think that in addition to introduction of an outstanding forward, a very good left-foot forward should be introduced too. </seg>
<seg id="32"> Except Xing Rui, who played on the Taishan Team several years ago, there has not been a real left-foot player on the team. </seg>
<seg id="33"> Although some players like Cui Peng can play the role, a real left-foot forward would be much better than one who is a guest player. </seg>
<seg id="34"> If these three issues can be solved well, the path for the Taishan Team to seize the championship should be somewhat smoother. </seg>
<seg id="35"> As a Shandong football fan, I really hope that the Taishan Team will be able to seize the championship this year. </seg>
<seg id="36"> But frankly speaking, the Taishan Team is very hopeful, but has no full guarantee of winning the championship this year. </seg>
</doc>
